examples/support_bot/README.md
     1‚Üí# Support bot
     3‚ÜíThis example is a customer service bot which includes a user interface agent and a help center agent with several tools.
     4‚ÜíThis example uses the helper function `run_demo_loop`, which allows us to create an interactive Swarm session.
     5‚Üí
     6‚Üí## Overview
     8‚ÜíThe support bot consists of two main agents:
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí1. **User Interface Agent**: Handles initial user interactions and directs them to the help center agent based on their needs.
    11‚Üí2. **Help Center Agent**: Provides detailed help and support using various tools and integrated with a Qdrant VectorDB for documentation retrieval.
    12‚Üí
    13‚Üí## Setup
    15‚ÜíTo start the support bot:
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí1. Ensure Docker is installed and running on your system.
    18‚Üí2. Install the necessary additional libraries:
    19‚Üí
    20‚Üí```shell
    21‚Üímake install
    22‚Üí```
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí3. Initialize docker
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí```shell
    27‚Üídocker-compose up -d
    28‚Üí```
    29‚Üí
    30‚Üí4. Prepare the vector DB:
    31‚Üí
    32‚Üí```shell
    33‚Üímake prep
    34‚Üí```
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí5. Run the main scripy:
    37‚Üí
    38‚Üí```shell
    39‚Üímake run
    40‚Üí```

